{
  "text": "Then, since the only possibility at this particular time, as I see it, was a polarization for service to others, I must assume from what you said that even though all were aware of this service to others necessity, they were unable to achieve it. What was the configuration of mind of the mind-body-spirit complexes at that time? Were they aware of the necessity for polarization or unaware of it? And if so, why did they have such a difficult time serving others to the extent necessary for graduation since this was the only polarity possible? Consider if you will the tendency of those who are divinely happy, as you call this a distortion, to have little urge to alter or better their condition. Such is the result of the mind-body spirit, which is not complex. There is the possibility of love of other selves and a service to other selves. But there is the overwhelming awareness of the creator in the self. The security is total.",
